%% KEEL — Flow 1: Create Vault (one atomic PTB — the TradeCap never exists outside the box)
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  actor Leo as Leader (Leo)
  participant Web as apps/web /create wizard
  participant Sui as Sui chain (one PTB)
  participant KC as keel_core::vault
  participant DB as deepbook::balance_manager

  Leo->>Web: Step 1 — pick strategy (Copy-delegate / DCA)
  Leo->>Web: Step 2 — params + policy (budget 5,000 · SUI/DBUSDC only · max 400/order · 30d · fee 10%)
  Web-->>Leo: plain-English policy + "what this vault can NEVER do"
  Leo->>Web: Step 3 — review, sign once

  Web->>Sui: PTB { 4 commands, all-or-nothing }
  activate Sui
  Sui->>DB: 1. balance_manager::new() → BalanceManager
  Sui->>DB: 2. mint_trade_cap(&mut bm) → TradeCap
  Sui->>KC: 3. create_vault(trade_cap, policy, fees, leader)
  Note over KC: TradeCap moved INTO Vault struct.<br/>Born locked. No wallet ever holds it.<br/>leader_min_stake enforced on first deposit.
  Sui->>KC: 4. share_object(Vault) + share(BalanceManager)
  KC-->>Sui: emit VaultCreated{id, leader, policy}
  deactivate Sui

  Sui-->>Web: digest + object ids
  Web-->>Leo: vault page live · listed on /vaults
  Note over Leo,DB: Atomicity = the security property:<br/>no intermediate state where the cap is stealable.
